      • getCoordinateMap

        public CoordinateMap getCoordinateMap(int sliceViewMode,
                                      int slice,
                                      int ivalue)
        Gets the coordinate mapping that should be the default for this data. Defaults to calling getCoordinateMap().
        Parameters:
        sliceViewMode - the slice orientation to display CNUDimensions.TRANSVERSE, CNUDimensions.CORONAL, or CNUDimensions.SAGITTAL
        slice - the slice number in the range from 0 to the number of slices for the sliceViewMode
        ivalue - the 4th or i dimension to use for displaying a slice from 4 dimensional data
        Returns:
        coordinate mapping object or null
